_json.description: When you're changing wall colorsat an inside corner, it can be hardto get a nice straight line, especiallyif the corner is rounded orhas built-up layers of paint. The trickis to paint around the corner withthe first color. Then when thepaint dries, mask off the paintedside using top-quality edge-sealingpainter's tape (FrogTape Multi-Surface is one example available from amazon.com).
